This paper deals with the characterization of interference in cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of mathematical models and analytical expressions to obtain statistics, which suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of full-duplex radios and device-to-device communications, which are topics related to multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Voronoi guard regions, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and game theory (cs.GT). However, since the paper focuses more on the analysis of interference in cellular networks, cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely categories.
